org.jconfigurations

Annotation Type CollectionConfiguration


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=FIELD)
public @interface CollectionConfiguration
    The CollectionConfigurator acts upon fields marked with @CollectionConfiguration. This annotation is designed to be used with fields that implement or extend the Collection interface.
    Author:
    George Aristy
    See Also:
    CollectionConfigurator

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      Class<? extends CollectionConfigurationConverter> converter
      Specifies the CollectionConfigurator to use to set the Collection field's value.
      String delimiter
      The configuration value's string representation will be tokenized using this delimiter value.
      Class<? extends ConfigurationConverter> elementConverter
      After the configuration value's string representation is tokenized using the specified delimiter, an instance of this ConfigurationConverter is used to convert each token to the appropriate type before being added to the field's collection-type implementation.

    • Element Detail

      • delimiter

        public abstract String delimiter
        The configuration value's string representation will be tokenized using this delimiter value. Each token will then be converted to the appropriate type before being added to the field's collection-type implementation.
        Returns:
        See Also:
        elementConverter()
        Default:
        ","

      • converter

        public abstract Class<? extends CollectionConfigurationConverter> converter
        Specifies the CollectionConfigurator to use to set the Collection field's value. If none is specified, then a default one is used from org.jconfigurations.converters. If no default converter is found then a ConfigurationException will be thrown.
        Returns:
        See Also:
        CollectionConfigurationConverter, CollectionFieldConverterFunction, DefaultCollectionTypeConverterFunction
        Default:
        org.jconfigurations.converters.NoCollectionConfigurationConverter.class

      • elementConverter

        public abstract Class<? extends ConfigurationConverter> elementConverter
        After the configuration value's string representation is tokenized using the specified delimiter, an instance of this ConfigurationConverter is used to convert each token to the appropriate type before being added to the field's collection-type implementation. If NoConfigurationConverter is specified (by default), then an available ConfigurationConverter will be used from org.jconfigurations.converters.
        Returns:
        See Also:
        delimiter(), DefaultTypeConverterFunction, FieldConverterFunction
        Default:
        org.jconfigurations.converters.NoConfigurationConverter.class
